Measure cereal in large microwaveable bowl. In 2-cup microwaveable measuring cup, microwave butter on High 30 seconds or until melted; stir in corn syrup and cocoa. Microwave on High 30 seconds or until mixture is boiling. Pour over cereal until coated. Microwave on High about 3 minutes, stirring every minute. Stir in dried cherries. Pour onto waxed-paper or foil-lined pan. Microwave white chocolate or chips on High about 30 seconds to 1 minute, until they can be stirred smooth. Pour into small zip-type bag, snip tiny corner and drizzle over top. Store tightly covered.